            <div><p>These are all in VertiCans but they are temporarily sitting in half-full buckets of water instead of in a stationary S.I.T.E.</p><p>They are preparing themselves and growing in number, eventually on their way to evenly spaced pentagons.</p><p>The pentagons have one VertiCan at each vertex. The pentagons are connected with Skeletron segments.Â </p><p>Growing these big pentagons continually, they can form dodecahedra at "human scale", the core of 6ft tall balls of vegetation that we release into creeks feeding local watersheds.</p></div>
      
